======================================================================
ALGEBRAIC ANALYSIS: prod(Q_k) for Interval
======================================================================

  n=5, m=2:
    prod Q_k = 1.000000
    prod sin(m*pi*k/n) = 0.312500
    prod sin(pi*k/n) = 0.312500
    n/2^(n-1) = 0.312500
    ratio = 1.000000
    ratio^2 = 1.000000
    => gcd(m,n)=1: m*k permutes residues mod n
    => prod sin(m*pi*k/n) = prod sin(pi*k/n)
    => prod Q_k = 1  QED

